<Link id="l00680" /><CodeLine lineNumber="680"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00681" /><CodeLine lineNumber="681"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Merge 2 debug locations and apply it to the Instruction. If the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00682" /><CodeLine lineNumber="682"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// instruction is a CallIns, we need to traverse the inline chain to find</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00683" /><CodeLine lineNumber="683"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// the common scope. This is not efficient for N-way merging as each time</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00684" /><CodeLine lineNumber="684"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// you merge 2 iterations, you need to rebuild the hashmap to find the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00685" /><CodeLine lineNumber="685"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// common scope. However, we still choose this API because:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00686" /><CodeLine lineNumber="686"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///  1) Simplicity: it takes 2 locations instead of a list of locations.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00687" /><CodeLine lineNumber="687"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///  2) In worst case, it increases the complexity from O(N&#42;I) to</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00688" /><CodeLine lineNumber="688"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///     O(2&#42;N&#42;I), where N is # of Instructions to merge, and I is the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00689" /><CodeLine lineNumber="689"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///     maximum level of inline stack. So it is still linear.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00690" /><CodeLine lineNumber="690"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///  3) Merging of call instructions should be extremely rare in real</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00691" /><CodeLine lineNumber="691"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///     applications, thus the N-way merging should be in code path.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00692" /><CodeLine lineNumber="692"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// The DebugLoc attached to this instruction will be overwritten by the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00693" /><CodeLine lineNumber="693"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// merged DebugLoc.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00694" /><CodeLine lineNumber="694"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">void</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> applyMergedLocation(DILocation &#42;LocA, DILocation &#42;LocB);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00695" /><CodeLine lineNumber="695"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00700" /><CodeLine lineNumber="700"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">void</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> updateLocationAfterHoist();</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00709" /><CodeLine lineNumber="709"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00710" /><CodeLine lineNumber="710"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Merge the DIAssignID metadata from this instruction and those attached to</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00711" /><CodeLine lineNumber="711"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// instructions in \\p SourceInstructions. This process performs a RAUW on</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00712" /><CodeLine lineNumber="712"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// the MetadataAsValue uses of the merged DIAssignID nodes. Not every</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00713" /><CodeLine lineNumber="713"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// instruction in \\p SourceInstructions needs to have DIAssignID</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00714" /><CodeLine lineNumber="714"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// metadata. If none of them do then nothing happens. If this instruction</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00715" /><CodeLine lineNumber="715"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// does not have a DIAssignID attachment but at least one in \\p</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00716" /><CodeLine lineNumber="716"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// SourceInstructions does then the merged one will be attached to</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00717" /><CodeLine lineNumber="717"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// it. However, instructions without attachments in \\p SourceInstructions</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00718" /><CodeLine lineNumber="718"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// are not modified.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00719" /><CodeLine lineNumber="719"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">void</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> mergeDIAssignID(ArrayRef&lt;<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> Instruction &#42;&gt; SourceInstructions);</Highlight></CodeLine>
